# Text Preprocessing
The IMDB movie review dataset was preprocessed before training the models.
The preprocessing steps are as follows:
1. Converted all text to lowercase to maintain consistency.
2. Removed punctuation marks and special characters.
3. Removed numerical values that do not contribute to sentiment prediction.
4. Tokenized the reviews into individual words.
5. Removed English stopwords such as "the", "is", and "was".
6. Applied TF-IDF Vectorization for the Machine Learning models.
7. Applied Tokenization and Sequence Padding for the LSTM model.
These preprocessing techniques reduced noise in the dataset and improved model performance.
